<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3AFFA3FADC3CF3FAB4D6C4" bold="true" box="[1342,1374,1936,1960]" pageId="12" pageNumber="565">27.</emphasis>
Right epandrial lamella, lateral view; 
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3AFFA3FE353CD7FE1DD6A0" bold="true" box="[471,503,1972,1996]" pageId="12" pageNumber="565">28.</emphasis>
Hypandrium and phallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BF536E4AE3BFFA2FF253A44FCC1D0E5" blockId="13.[151,1437,151,898]" pageId="13" pageNumber="566">Abdomen apically weakly curved downward, somewhat shiny blackish with gray pollinosity. Hypopygium narrower than pregenital segments. Hairs and bristles on abdomen dark yellow, except those on hypopygium blackish. Hypopygium distinctly narrower than pregenital segments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF536E4AE3BFFA2FF253AF0FD21D30D" blockId="13.[151,1437,151,898]" pageId="13" pageNumber="566">
Terminalia (
<figureCitation id="13712A61AE3BFFA2FEB03AF0FE30D0C1" box="[338,474,402,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–28" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[176,1415,190,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-23@12.[163,1424,181,1912]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 25–28. Oedalea yangi sp. nov. (male). 25. Genitalia, dorsal view; 26. Left epandrial lamella, lateral view; 27. Right epandrial lamella, lateral view; 28. Hypandrium and phallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598028" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598028/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="566">Figs 25–28</figureCitation>
): Left and right cerci (
<figureCitation id="13712A61AE3BFFA2FD073AF0FCD3D0C1" box="[741,825,402,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–28" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[176,1415,190,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-23@12.[163,1424,181,1912]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 25–28. Oedalea yangi sp. nov. (male). 25. Genitalia, dorsal view; 26. Left epandrial lamella, lateral view; 27. Right epandrial lamella, lateral view; 28. Hypandrium and phallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598028" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598028/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="566">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
) digitiform, apically slightly narrowed. Basal bridge of epandrium (
<figureCitation id="13712A61AE3BFFA2FEDD3AD4FE78D0BD" box="[319,402,438,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–28" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[176,1415,190,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-23@12.[163,1424,181,1912]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 25–28. Oedalea yangi sp. nov. (male). 25. Genitalia, dorsal view; 26. Left epandrial lamella, lateral view; 27. Right epandrial lamella, lateral view; 28. Hypandrium and phallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598028" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598028/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="566">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
) narrow; left and right epandrial lamellae (
<figureCitation id="13712A61AE3BFFA2FC9F3AD4FC3AD0BD" box="[893,976,438,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–28" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[176,1415,190,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-23@12.[163,1424,181,1912]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 25–28. Oedalea yangi sp. nov. (male). 25. Genitalia, dorsal view; 26. Left epandrial lamella, lateral view; 27. Right epandrial lamella, lateral view; 28. Hypandrium and phallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598028" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598028/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="566">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
) wide and not narrowed apically (dorsal view). Right epandrial lamella (
<figureCitation id="13712A61AE3BFFA2FE1D3AB8FDBBD099" box="[511,593,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–28" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[176,1415,190,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-23@12.[163,1424,181,1912]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 25–28. Oedalea yangi sp. nov. (male). 25. Genitalia, dorsal view; 26. Left epandrial lamella, lateral view; 27. Right epandrial lamella, lateral view; 28. Hypandrium and phallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598028" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598028/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="566">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
) trapezoidal (lateral view); right surstylus 1.5 times longer than wide, apically slightly curved ventrally. Left epandrial lamella (
<figureCitation id="13712A61AE3BFFA2FCE43A9CFCB0D376" box="[774,858,511,538]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–28" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[176,1415,190,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-23@12.[163,1424,181,1912]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 25–28. Oedalea yangi sp. nov. (male). 25. Genitalia, dorsal view; 26. Left epandrial lamella, lateral view; 27. Right epandrial lamella, lateral view; 28. Hypandrium and phallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598028" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598028/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="566">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
) trapezoidal (lateral view); left surstylus 1.1 times longer than wide, widened apically with apical margin obliquely incised (lateral view). Hypandrium (
<figureCitation id="13712A61AE3BFFA2FB1D3940FAA5D351" box="[1279,1359,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–28" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[176,1415,190,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-23@12.[163,1424,181,1912]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 25–28. Oedalea yangi sp. nov. (male). 25. Genitalia, dorsal view; 26. Left epandrial lamella, lateral view; 27. Right epandrial lamella, lateral view; 28. Hypandrium and phallus, ventral view. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6598028" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6598028/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="566">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
) much longer than wide, apically without lateral incision.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF536E4AE3BFFA2FF253908FE48D3E9" blockId="13.[151,1437,151,898]" box="[199,418,619,645]" pageId="13" pageNumber="566">
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3BFFA2FF253908FECFD3E9" bold="true" box="[199,293,619,645]" pageId="13" pageNumber="566">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
