<subSubSection id="C350656FAE3BFFA2FF253998FCD0D231" pageId="13" pageNumber="566" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF536E4AE3BFFA2FF253998FCD0D231" blockId="13.[151,1437,151,898]" pageId="13" pageNumber="566">
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3BFFA2FF253998FED1D279" bold="true" box="[199,315,763,789]" pageId="13" pageNumber="566">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D67AE3BFFA2FCE03998FC34D279" authority="Frey" authorityName="Frey" authorityYear="1953" box="[770,990,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Oedalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="566" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicornis">
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3BFFA2FCE03998FC49D279" box="[770,931,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="566">O. longicornis</emphasis>
Frey
</taxonomicName>
, but may be separated from the latter by the following features: antenna 1.8 times as long as head, palpus brown to black. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D67AE3BFFA2FBAD387CFB18D255" authorityName="Frey" authorityYear="1953" box="[1103,1266,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Oedalea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="566" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicornis">
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3BFFA2FBAD387CFB18D255" box="[1103,1266,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="566">O. longicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the antenna is 1.5 times as long as head height and the palpus is yellowish.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C350656FAE3BFFA2FF253804FBB1D2EE" box="[199,1115,871,898]" pageId="13" pageNumber="566" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BF536E4AE3BFFA2FF253804FBB1D2EE" blockId="13.[151,1437,151,898]" box="[199,1115,871,898]" pageId="13" pageNumber="566">
<emphasis id="B93EEAF6AE3BFFA2FF253804FEA4D2ED" bold="true" box="[199,334,871,897]" pageId="13" pageNumber="566">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named after the collector, Mr. Qicheng Yang (Wuhan).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
